<h1>Kevin Marsden</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://kmarsden.com/now/">kmarsden.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Folsom
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Happiness Engineer at Automattic (makers of WordPress.com)
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help people build websites and resolve technical issues
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I really enjoy the combination of helping people and solving difficult problems.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
I'm finding success forming new habits by writing down a habit checklist every day.  Every morning I write down: push-ups, pull-ups, run/walk, floss, and no alcohol and then check them off as I accomplish each task.  The act of writing it down and creating active habit streaks is helpful and motivating.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
All the Light We Cannot See by Anthony Doerr
</p>

